<br>
I hope the next Naggy raid will go more smoothly since I still have not seen this big ugly lizard.  I will see you at the next Vox raid and will most likely still be lvl52. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As for all of the problems I have some suggestions to solving them, some you may like and some you may not... the policies in place are fine but these are just my ideas to what might make the raid go more smoothly:<br>
<br>
1- The possibility of raising the minimum lvl for raiding to lvl45 so you will have a little less people but hopefully some more experienced people.<br>
2- If people are not doing what they are told... don't be nice, just kick them out and maybe they will learn.  I know you are just a very nice person but people might be getting the impression that they can get away with stuff and I don't think that should happen.<br>
3- Possibly make the raids sign up only and have a limited number of people allowed and call the roll once you have that amount.<br>
4- Don't let people join a dragon raid late unless they had already posted on the board that they will be late.<br>
5- If people fuss about loot in any way then maybe ban them from rolling on items.  These raids are not to be attended for the sole reason of gaining &quot;uber&quot; loot.  I myself have attended the Vox raids because the thrill of killing a dragon excites me and is very fun.<br>
<br>
Again, I know some people will disagree with what I have just posted, but these are MY opinions and mine alone.<br>
<br>
 <br>
I would like to thank all of the support team, raid leaders and especially Azure for having an uncharted amount of patience in dealing with the poor manered people that attended this raid.  I would also like to thank the raiders who made it less stressful to the raid leaders by not whining, complaining and bickering about loot. <p><p>
