<br>
As to Nottys comment that this was the worst raid, in terms of behavior, that he had seen, I have seen far worse. The first Vox raid I attended was far worse. People were questioning every facet of the entire raid right up to the point of the inevitable TPW. That raid was a resounding failure, not because of Kommisars leadership, but because no one was following orders and constantly objected to every single one of Kommisars instructions. It was my first Dragon raid so I didn't realize then how bad it was then, I do now.<br>
<br>
One thing Primortius said I do have to disagree with. You said that the decisions of the raid leadership should not be questioned on this board. I disagree. If a person has an issue with how something in a raid is handled, this is the only place to bring up the issue. Not in ooc. not in shout. not by tell bombing the raid leadership during the raid. If issues aren't raised here, how can they be resolved? Although I was around when KCoG formed back in 1999 I was more concerened with taking the boat to freeport safely than with such things as planes and Dragon raids so I can't say for sure but it would be my guess that it took a lot of trial and error before KCoG got to the point that we are at today in regards to our ability do take down the Dragons. This undoubtedly involved a good deal of questioning the tactics of the raid leadership and thoughtful (hopefully) discussion of the issues that arose during each raid. If we are to continue to grow and improve the only way we can do that is thru discussion and feedback on issues when they arise. How can a problem be addressed and rectified if no one raises the issue? you say that there is no reason to questin anything that was done at the raid. I'm sorry but again, I can't agree. This is not a Dictatorship. I agree totally that during the raid you follow orders period. But if issues arise that yone feels need adressing, people not only should bring them here but would be derelict in their duty to KCoG if they didn't raise issues that occurr. There has been a long tradition of bringing issues and problems to this board. That is a large part of what KCog is here for, a forum where people can raise issues and work out solutions. Our server is unique in having a community that does this. I didn't bring up issues to complain nor to challenge the raid leaderships abilities. If you read my previous posts you will see that I have nothing but praise for the abilities of the raid leadership and respect for the decisions that were made. But I had issues with how some things were handled and so I raised those issues here and have had them addressed.<br>
<br>
As for stating that people should step up if they think they can do better, and I pretty much said the same thing, if this is being directed at myself, Destructress , or Kcarcreve you are barking up the wrong tree. Our guild has stepped up to lead planes raids for KCoG. We know what it is like to try and control a daycare with the koolaid spiked with acid. That is why we brought these issues to this board for meaningful discussion. When Kommisar stepped down form leading Dragon raids, we seriously considering leading those but the random nature of dragon raids and our work schedules made that impossible and Azure has stepped up and has done a fantastic job. If this is being direccted at those who don't follow orders and continually question the raid leaders direction in public channels during the raid, I couldn't agree more.<br>
<br>
I doubt I will check this post again as I have said all that I need to say and the issues that I raised have all been answered. Whether I personally agree with the reasoning behind some of the answers i will keep to myself as it is not relevant as long as i am not the raid leader. thanks again all for participating with your thoughts, suggestions, and answers. <p>Falcone Robinsbane<BR>
